  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nThe object returned from `useRef` is not the same on every render and the `initialValue` passed as argument does not reflect the `.current` value of the object.\r\nCodeSandbox showing this bug:  \r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/embed/8xz09962v8\r\nIf you click the button `Increment` the component will trigger an update and if you see the console tab the message displayed is repeated on every render, with the `.current` value being `null`.\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nThe same as the one written in the documentation: https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-reference.html#useref.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\nVersion 18.6.x\r\nChrome",
